Using tree-based models in a plug-and-play manner for clinical prediction may result in undesirable predictor-outcome associations. Therefore, we recommend carefully taking their behavior into account during modeling decisions and evaluations. Further research is needed to explore the potential value of recent developments in decision tree literature, such as using constraints to incorporate prior knowledge and using soft-split decision trees.
